Explain Hoisting?
It’s a mechanism where variables and function declaration to the top of the scope.
Are JavaScript initialization hoisted?
No. It has value undefined for var and for let and const no value get intialized.

Explain Temporal Dead Zone?
TDZ it’s a period or it’s a state of a variable where variables are named in memory but they are not 
initialized with any value. During this time if you try access the variable you will get initialized error.
Var                       vs                              Let

Scope Scoped to the                  vs             Scoped to the immediate 
Immediate function body.                            enclosing block.

Initialized value Value initialized   vs             Value initialized with nothing
with Undefined at hoisting                          at hoisting
